It&#8217;s believed the suspect was allegedly shot by a security guard after stealing porridge from a factory in the area. JOHANNESBURG - A man believed to be in his late 20s has been shot and killed in Pinetown, outside Durban in KwaZulu-Natal on Saturday afternoon.It s believed the suspect was allegedly shot by a security guard after stealing porridge from a factory in the area.Upon arrival on the scene, paramedics say they found the suspect lying in the middle of the road with a gunshot wound just below his heart.ER24 spokesperson Annine Sidall said, Unfortunately nothing could be done for the man and he was declared dead on the scene. Local authorities were on the scene for further investigation., 